{
  "texts": [
    "The MEC data collected in this paper includes not only textual data, but also device status, network traffic, user behavior, etc., most of which are semi-structured.",
    "There are three primary methods for converting these data into textual format: first, convert each item or group of data into descriptive sentences.",
    "For example, the device status can be converted to \"Device A has 80% battery and a signal strength of -60dBm\".",
    "Network traffic can be converted to \"User B's traffic consumption between 12:00 and 13:00 is 200MB\".",
    "Alternatively, convert the data into a series of event logs."
  ]
}